Use '--name <LegalName>' to specify a legal package name.
mason new bad-name --lib
Bad package name 'bad-name' - only Chapel identifiers are legal package names.
Use '--name <LegalName>' to specify a legal package name.
mason new bad.name
Bad package name 'bad.name' - only Chapel identifiers are legal package names.
Use '--name <LegalName>' to specify a legal package name.
