Use '--name <LegalName>' to specify a legal package name.
mason new 0bad --name good
Created new application project: good
Tip: To convert existing code to a mason project, move the driver application to the `src/good.chpl` file. For adding other source code, using submodules is the recommended approach to avoid namespace collisions.
cat Mason.toml
[brick]
name="good"
version="0.1.0"
license="None"
type="application"

[dependencies]
mason init --name good
